{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17655111","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17655111"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:59:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:59:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18650"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18650","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18650"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.26,0,0.72,0.02,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11382"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114976"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11382","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11382"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18650"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96982"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6674"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26395"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26646"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26940"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114976","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114976"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe cerebral hemispheres receive their arterial blood supply from three major vessels that branch from the circle of Willis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the distribution of the middle cerebral artery?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Supplies the medial surface of the cerebral hemisphere","Supplies only the frontal lobe","Supplies most of the lateral surface of the cerebral hemisphere","Supplies only the occipital lobe","Supplies only the temporal lobe"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emiddle cerebral artery supplies most of the lateral surface of the cerebral hemisphere\u003C/strong\u003E, including the lateral parts of the frontal, parietal and temporal lobes. This distribution includes critical functional areas such as the primary motor cortex, primary sensory cortex and Wernicke area.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe medial surface of the cerebral hemisphere is the territory of the anterior cerebral artery. While the middle cerebral artery does supply parts of the frontal and temporal lobes, it supplies much more than just these individual areas. The occipital lobe is primarily supplied by the posterior cerebral artery. Understanding the distribution of cerebral arteries is crucial for interpreting the clinical effects of stroke affecting different vascular territories.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The middle cerebral artery supplies most of the lateral surface of the cerebral hemisphere including primary motor and sensory areas.","The anterior cerebral artery supplies the medial surface of the cerebral hemisphere and a narrow strip of the lateral surface.","The posterior cerebral artery supplies the occipital lobe and inferior temporal lobe."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96982"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18650"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96982","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96982"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-21T18:00:19+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-21T18:02:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"